In 1989, to celebrate the strip's 40th anniversary, GRP Records released a soundtrack album with the same title as the TV special.[1] The soundtrack contains versions of music and songs from the TV specials, as well as some original compositions, performed by various jazz artists, such as David Benoit, Dave Grusin, Lee Ritenour and Kenny G.
